00:04:02.900 --> 00:04:07.300
with by using your iPhone, call
people or text them or whatnot.

00:04:07.300 --> 00:04:09.450
And your contacts are synced to the desktop.

00:04:09.449 --> 00:04:17.909
So again, using iTunes you would sync your contacts
between your Address Book on Mac OS and the iPhone.

00:04:17.910 --> 00:04:21.330
And iPhone 2.0 introduced ActiveSync.

00:04:21.329 --> 00:04:28.120
So it might also have your work contacts from your
office environment on the iPhone using ActiveSync.

00:04:28.120 --> 00:04:35.620
And new in iPhone 3.0 is the ability to
connect to your corporate directory using LDAP.

00:04:35.620 --> 00:04:42.470
So that's something we introduced in 3.0 and
sometimes that can be a little bit tricky to configure.

00:04:42.470 --> 00:04:46.370
So if you're not familiar with iPhone Configuration Utility,

00:04:46.370 --> 00:04:51.220
I highly recommend that you take a
look at that on Apple's download site.

00:04:51.220 --> 00:04:57.830
